snippet.textDisplay: 5:25 Its dope, L2 Cache is in serious short supply in chips, having more means that games with a few rapid update functions (like an online MP), can use the bonus cache to store the functions it requires on each duty cycle. Normally L3 would be used (significantly slower), which is a pretty big upgrade overall, making L2 usable for whole processes, instead of just the average read//write opcodes
